                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>Throughout the Ms.:</item>
                           <item>ይ፡ ካ፡ for ይቤ፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይ፡ ሕ፡ for ይቤ፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                           <item>ይ፡ ዲ፡ for ይቤ፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                           <item>በ፡/በእ፡ for በእንተ፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the donor; incipits and
                           headings of the texts und their sections; directives for the ministers or
                           their abbreviations, partly the musical notation signs; the word kāʿǝba;
                           elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1v">ff. 1v-2</locus>
                           <desc>r (bottom): Excerpt from Säʿatat za-lelit “Horologium for the
                              Night” (MSLN p. 18).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>: [n.l.]  ኢዩሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ጥዑመ፡ ስም፡ ዘጸዋፅኮ፡
                              ለጳውሎስ፡ ጸውዐነ፡ ውስት፡ ከብከብከ፡ [ዘበሰማያት፡] … </quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The excerpt is crudely written in pen, barely legible. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#2ra">f. 2ra</locus>
                           <desc>-vb: Excerpt from the Gospel of John (Jn. 10:1-13).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the same hand that wrote Additiones 4 and 5. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#29va">ff. 29va</locus>
                           <desc>-30rb: Excerpt from the Daily Office Prayers and Litanies.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#29va">29va</locus>: ወካዕበ፡ ናስተበቍዕ፡ ዘኵሎ፡
                              ይእሕዝ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አብ፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in bleak black ink. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#159ra">f. 159ra</locus>
                           <desc>-rb: Excerpt from the Gospel of Matthew (Mt. 26:26-29).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the same hand that wrote Additiones 2 and 5. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#159rb">ff. 159rb-160</locus>
                           <desc>rb: Excerpt from the Gospel of Luke (Lk.1:39-56).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the same hand that wrote Additiones 2 and 4. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title ቅዳሴ is written on the front board with green
                           modern paint.
 - The scribe wrote in compressed script on <locus from="8vb" to="10ra">8vb-10ra</locus>.
 - Cues for rubrication
                           (incipit of sections) on <locus from="27r" to="28vb">27r-28vb</locus>
                           (Text VI) and <locus from="32r" to="36v">32r-36v</locus>, 50v-52v (Text
                           VIII).
 - Omitted letters or words inserted interlineally: e.g.,
                              <locus target="#8rb">8rb</locus>, 8vb, 18rb, 37rb, 39ra, 51ra, 54rb,
                           108va.
 - Tamallas-signs (in the shapes of ┴) indicating the place
                           where the omissions, written in the margins, belong: <locus target="#13rb">13rb</locus>, 18rb, 19vb, 23va, 26rb, 28rb, 29rb, 90va,
                           113rab, 119vb, 124vb, 125vb, 129rab, 132ra, 136ra, 139rb, 140ra, 146rb,
                           158ra.
 - Corrections written over erasures: <locus target="#24vb">24vb</locus>, 57vb, 73va, 141va, 153ra.
 - Erasures marked with
                           thin lines: e.g., <locus target="#82ra">82ra</locus>, 122va, 131rb,
                           147rb.
 - Pen trial: <locus target="#31r">31r</locus>
 - Crude
                           notes in recent hands, barely legible: <locus target="#11v">11v</locus>,
                           30v, 160v.
 - Scribbles: <locus target="#24v">24v</locus>, 25r, 32r,
                           33r, 60v, 103r, 158vb.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Abbreviated terms for the reading of Text VI are
                              written in the margins or intercolumns of fols. 27r-28v.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
